<title>USA: Faulding converts pfd shares into common. [CORRECTED 17:45 GMT]</title>
<headline>Faulding converts pfd shares into common. [CORRECTED 17:45 GMT]</headline>
<dateline>ELIZABETH, N.J. 1997-06-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Faulding Inc said Monday its majority shareholder Faulding Holdings Inc will convert its preferred Faulding stock into common stock.</p>
<p>Faulding Holdings will convert 834,188 shares of class A preferred stock at ratio of 1 to 6 into 5,005,128 shares of common stock.</p>
<p>(Corrects to make clear Faulding Holdings Inc is a wholly-owned subsidiary of F.H Faulding &amp; Co Ltd, not of Faulding Inc).</p>
<p>After the conversion, Faulding Holdings will own 71.1 percent of Faulding common stock, up from 61.5 percent.</p>
